'''Tim D. Seip''' is a [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] member of the [[Pennsylvania House of Representatives]] for the [[Pennsylvania House of Representatives, District 125|125th legislative district]]. He was elected in [[Pennsylvania House of Representatives elections, 2006|2006]]<ref>{{cite web | title = 2006 General Election - Representative in the General Assembly| work = Commonwealth of PA - Elections Information | publisher = Pennsylvania Department of State | date = 2004 | url = http://www.electionreturns.state.pa.us/ElectionsInformation.aspx?FunctionID=13&ElectionID=24&OfficeID=13| accessdate = 2009-01-09}}</ref>.  

Seip graduated from [[Mansfield University]] with a degree in Criminal Justice Administration and [[Marywood University]], with a master's in Social Work.<ref name=bio>{{cite web | title = Rep. Tim D. Seip Biography | publisher = Pennsylvania House Democratic Caucus | date = 2008 | url = http://www.pahouse.com/Seip/bio.asp | accessdate = 2008-11-15 }}</ref> Prior to elective office, he worked as a social worker at various locations.<ref name=votesmart>{{cite web | title = Representative Tim Seip (PA)| work = Project Vote Smart| publisher = Project Vote Smart| date = 2008| url = http://www.votesmart.org/bio.php?can_id=60254| accessdate =2009-01-09}}</ref>
